<% provide(:title, 'User Roles') %>

<div class="page_header">
  <h1>User Roles</h1>
  <div>User roles are not intended to exactly identify the role of an employee. They are to represent the privileges of an employee.</div>
</div>

<div class="page-header-small">
  <h1>Corporate/App Support</h1>
</div>
<div class="alert">
  These roles have access to <b class='blue-text'>all</b> jobs and data. They can read and write.
</div>
<div class="list">
  <%= render UserRole.support_roles current_user.company %>
</div>
<br><br>

<div class="page-header-small">
  <h1>Field</h1>
</div>
<div class="alert">
  These roles have access to <b class='blue-text'>only</b> to the jobs they are assigned. The exception are the manager roles which can access everything within the district.
</div>
<div class="list">
  <%= render UserRole.field_roles current_user.company %>
</div>
<br><br>

<div class="page-header-small">
  <h1>Sales</h1>
</div>
<div class="alert">
  These roles have access to <b class='blue-text'>all</b> jobs and data. They can read and write.
</div>
<div class="list">
  <%= render UserRole.sales_roles current_user.company %>
</div>
<br><br>

<div class="page-header-small">
  <h1>Elephant Admin</h1>
</div>
<div class="alert">
  These roles only have access to the <b class='blue-text'>CCT</b> (Company Configuration Tool) for configuring the company and have no access to job data.
</div>
<div class="list">
  <%= render UserRole.admin_roles current_user.company %>
</div>

